  "title": "Maintenance Technician (Country Club)",
  "description": "<p>Our client is one of Singapore’s most prestigious golf and lifestyle clubs, offering premier recreational and social facilities.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Job Scope:</strong></p><ul><li>Lead and oversee all maintenance, repair, and servicing of golf course machinery, equipment, and buggies.</li><li>Troubleshoot mechanical issues, perform preventive maintenance, and ensure smooth equipment operations.</li><li>Manage spare parts ordering, vendor quotations, and workshop inventory with accurate reporting.</li><li>Supervise and coordinate a team of maintenance staff to deliver efficient and timely work.</li><li>Support the Course Superintendent in budgeting, cost control, and resource planning.</li><li>Ensure workshop safety, cleanliness, and compliance with operational standards.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 2 years’ hands-on experience in mechanical maintenance and repairs.</li><li>Strong technical, troubleshooting, and organizational skills with attention to detail.</li><li>Good teamwork and communication abilities to manage staff and vendors.</li></ul><p>Working hours: Mon-Fri 6.30am - 4.00pm</p><p>Working location: Thomson</p><p><br /></p><p>Salary: Up to $3,500 + AWS + performance bonus</p><p><br /></p><p>To apply, kindly click <strong>APPLY NOW</strong> to submit your latest CV.</p><p><br /></p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>",
